24#include <windows.h>

27#if defined(WEBRTC_WIN)
28#define LAST_SYSTEM_ERROR (::GetLastError())
29#elif defined(__native_client__) && __native_client__
30#define LAST_SYSTEM_ERROR (0)
31#elif defined(WEBRTC_POSIX)
32#include <errno.h>
33#define LAST_SYSTEM_ERROR (errno)
34#endif // WEBRTC_WIN

38namespace {
39
40RTC_NORETURN void WriteFatalLogAndAbort(const std::string& output) {
41 const char* output_c = output.c_str();
42#if defined(WEBRTC_ANDROID)
43 __android_log_print(ANDROID_LOG_ERROR, RTC_LOG_TAG_ANDROID, "%s\n", output_c);
44#endif
45 fflush(stdout);
46 fprintf(stderr, "%s", output_c);
47 fflush(stderr);
48#if defined(WEBRTC_WIN)
49 DebugBreak();
50#endif
51 abort();
52}
53
54#if defined(__GNUC__)
55__attribute__((__format__(__printf__, 2, 3)))
56#endif
57void AppendFormat(std::string* s, const char* fmt, ...) {
58 va_list args, copy;
59 va_start(args, fmt);
60 va_copy(copy, args);
61 const int predicted_length = std::vsnprintf(nullptr, 0, fmt, copy);
62 va_end(copy);
63
64 if (predicted_length > 0) {
65 const size_t size = s->size();
66 s->resize(size + predicted_length);
67 // Pass "+ 1" to vsnprintf to include space for the '\0'.
68 std::vsnprintf(&((*s)[size]), predicted_length + 1, fmt, args);
69 }
70 va_end(args);
71}
72} // namespace
73
74namespace rtc {
75namespace webrtc_checks_impl {
76
77#if RTC_CHECK_MSG_ENABLED
78// Reads one argument from args, appends it to s and advances fmt.
79// Returns true iff an argument was sucessfully parsed.
80bool ParseArg(va_list* args, const CheckArgType** fmt, std::string* s) {
81 if (**fmt == CheckArgType::kEnd)
82 return false;
83
84 switch (**fmt) {
85 case CheckArgType::kInt:
86 AppendFormat(s, "%d", va_arg(*args, int));
87 break;
88 case CheckArgType::kLong:
89 AppendFormat(s, "%ld", va_arg(*args, long));
90 break;
91 case CheckArgType::kLongLong:
92 AppendFormat(s, "%lld", va_arg(*args, long long));
93 break;
94 case CheckArgType::kUInt:
95 AppendFormat(s, "%u", va_arg(*args, unsigned));
96 break;
97 case CheckArgType::kULong:
98 AppendFormat(s, "%lu", va_arg(*args, unsigned long));
99 break;
100 case CheckArgType::kULongLong:
101 AppendFormat(s, "%llu", va_arg(*args, unsigned long long));
102 break;
103 case CheckArgType::kDouble:
104 AppendFormat(s, "%g", va_arg(*args, double));
105 break;
106 case CheckArgType::kLongDouble:
107 AppendFormat(s, "%Lg", va_arg(*args, long double));
108 break;
109 case CheckArgType::kCharP:
110 s->append(va_arg(*args, const char*));
111 break;
112 case CheckArgType::kStdString:
113 s->append(*va_arg(*args, const std::string*));
114 break;
115 case CheckArgType::kStringView: {
116 const absl::string_view sv = *va_arg(*args, const absl::string_view*);
117 s->append(sv.data(), sv.size());
118 break;
119 }
120 case CheckArgType::kVoidP:
121 AppendFormat(s, "%p", va_arg(*args, const void*));
122 break;
123 default:
124 s->append("[Invalid CheckArgType]");
125 return false;
126 }
127 (*fmt)++;
128 return true;
129}
130
131RTC_NORETURN void FatalLog(const char* file,
132 int line,
133 const char* message,
134 const CheckArgType* fmt,
135 ...) {
136 va_list args;
137 va_start(args, fmt);
138
139 std::string s;
140 AppendFormat(&s,
141 "\n\n"
142 "#\n"
143 "# Fatal error in: %s, line %d\n"
144 "# last system error: %u\n"
145 "# Check failed: %s",
146 file, line, LAST_SYSTEM_ERROR, message);
147
148 if (*fmt == CheckArgType::kCheckOp) {
149 // This log message was generated by RTC_CHECK_OP, so we have to complete
150 // the error message using the operands that have been passed as the first
151 // two arguments.
152 fmt++;
153
154 std::string s1, s2;
155 if (ParseArg(&args, &fmt, &s1) && ParseArg(&args, &fmt, &s2))
156 AppendFormat(&s, " (%s vs. %s)\n# ", s1.c_str(), s2.c_str());
157 } else {
158 s.append("\n# ");
159 }
160
161 // Append all the user-supplied arguments to the message.
162 while (ParseArg(&args, &fmt, &s))
163 ;
164
165 va_end(args);
166
167 WriteFatalLogAndAbort(s);
168}
169#else // RTC_CHECK_MSG_ENABLED
170RTC_NORETURN void FatalLog(const char* file, int line) {
171 std::string s;
172 AppendFormat(&s,
173 "\n\n"
174 "#\n"
175 "# Fatal error in: %s, line %d\n"
176 "# last system error: %u\n"
177 "# Check failed.\n"
178 "# ",
179 file, line, LAST_SYSTEM_ERROR);
180 WriteFatalLogAndAbort(s);
181}
182#endif // RTC_CHECK_MSG_ENABLED
183
184#if RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON
185
186RTC_NORETURN void UnreachableCodeReached(const char* file, int line) {
187 std::string s;
188 AppendFormat(&s,
189 "\n\n"
190 "#\n"
191 "# Unreachable code reached: %s, line %d\n"
192 "# last system error: %u\n"
193 "# ",
194 file, line, LAST_SYSTEM_ERROR);
195 WriteFatalLogAndAbort(s);
196}
197
198#else // !RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON
199
200RTC_NORETURN void UnreachableCodeReached() {
201 std::string s;
202 AppendFormat(&s,
203 "\n\n"
204 "#\n"
205 "# Unreachable code reached (file and line unknown)\n"
206 "# last system error: %u\n"
207 "# ",
208 LAST_SYSTEM_ERROR);
209 WriteFatalLogAndAbort(s);
210}
211
212#endif // !RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON

215} // namespace rtc

217// Function to call from the C version of the RTC_CHECK and RTC_DCHECK macros.
218RTC_NORETURN void rtc_FatalMessage(const char* file,
219 int line,
220 const char* msg) {
221#if RTC_CHECK_MSG_ENABLED
222 static constexpr rtc::webrtc_checks_impl::CheckArgType t[] = {
223 rtc::webrtc_checks_impl::CheckArgType::kEnd};
224 rtc::webrtc_checks_impl::FatalLog(file, line, msg, t);
225#else
226 rtc::webrtc_checks_impl::FatalLog(file, line);
227#endif
228}
